+# Fix Summary: Dynamic Styles with Media Queries/Conditionals
+
+## Issue Description
+
+In StyleX version 0.14.3, a regression was introduced where dynamic styles that include media queries, pseudo-classes, or pseudo-elements would concatenate class names without spaces between them. This caused the styles to not be applied correctly at runtime because the concatenated class name (e.g., `"xcu4pi3x1cbl2y9"`) would not match any CSS classes.
+
+## Root Cause
+
+The issue was introduced in commit 7a1ed95a during a refactoring of the dynamic styles code. The original implementation included logic to add a space suffix to each class name except the last one:
+
+```javascript
+const suffix = index === classList.length - 1 ? '' : ' ';
+t.stringLiteral(cls + suffix)
+```
+
+In the refactored version, this space handling logic was removed, causing class names to be concatenated without spaces.
+
+## Solution
+
+The fix adds space separators between class names in the `classList.forEach` loop in `/testbed/packages/@stylexjs/babel-plugin/src/visitors/stylex-create.js`:
+
+```javascript
+classList.forEach((cls, index) => {
+  const expr = dynamicStyles.find(
+    ({ path }) => origClassPaths[cls] === path,
+  )?.expression;
+
+  if (expr && !isSafeToSkipNullCheck(expr)) {
+    isStatic = false;
+    exprList.push(
+      t.conditionalExpression(
+        t.binaryExpression('!=', expr, t.nullLiteral()),
+        t.stringLiteral(cls),
+        expr,
+      ),
+    );
+  } else {
+    exprList.push(t.stringLiteral(cls));
+  }
+  
+  // Add space after class, except for the last one
+  if (index < classList.length - 1) {
+    exprList.push(t.stringLiteral(' '));
+  }
+});
+```
+
+## Changes Made
+
+1. **Modified file**: `packages/@stylexjs/babel-plugin/src/visitors/stylex-create.js`
+   - Added `index` parameter to `classList.forEach` (line 332)
+   - Added space insertion logic after each class except the last one (lines 350-353)
+
+2. **Test updates**: 6 snapshot tests were automatically updated to reflect the correct output with spaces
+
+## Example Transformation
+
+### Before the fix:
+```javascript
+const example = {
+  dynamicMedia: () => [{
+    kWkggS: "xcu4pi3x1cbl2y9",  // ❌ Missing space - won't match CSS!
+    $$css: true
+  }, {}]
+};
+```
+
+### After the fix:
+```javascript
+const example = {
+  dynamicMedia: () => [{
+    kWkggS: "xcu4pi3" + " " + "x1cbl2y9",  // ✅ With space - correctly matches CSS!
+    $$css: true
+  }, {}]
+};
+```
+
+This correctly evaluates to `"xcu4pi3 x1cbl2y9"` which matches both CSS classes.
+
+## Test Results
+
+- ✅ All 700 tests pass
+- ✅ All 673 snapshots pass  
+- ✅ Edge cases handled correctly:
+  - Single class (no trailing space)
+  - Multiple classes with media queries
+  - Multiple classes with pseudo-classes
+  - Mixed dynamic and static properties
+  - Null-checked dynamic values
+  - Four or more conditional styles
+
+## Verification
+
+The fix has been verified with:
+1. The exact test case from the PR description
+2. Multiple edge cases including null checks
+3. The full existing test suite
+4. Custom comprehensive tests
+
+All tests confirm that dynamic styles with media queries and conditional styles now correctly generate class names with spaces between them.
