+# Fix for Dynamic Styles with Media Queries/Conditionals
+
+## Problem
+
+In StyleX version 0.14.3, a regression was introduced where dynamic styles that include media queries, pseudo-classes, or pseudo-elements would concatenate class names without spaces between them.
+
+### Example Issue
+
+Given this input:
+```javascript
+const example = stylex.create({
+  dynamicMedia: () => ({
+    backgroundColor: {
+      "@media (min-width:1024px)": "purple",
+      default: "gray",
+    },
+  }),
+});
+```
+
+**Before the fix**, the output was:
+```javascript
+const example = {
+  dynamicMedia: () => [{
+    kWkggS: "xcu4pi3x1cbl2y9",  // ❌ Missing space!
+    $$css: true
+  }, {}]
+};
+```
+
+This concatenates to `"xcu4pi3x1cbl2y9"` which doesn't match any CSS class.
+
+**After the fix**, the output is:
+```javascript
+const example = {
+  dynamicMedia: () => [{
+    kWkggS: "xcu4pi3" + " " + "x1cbl2y9",  // ✅ With space!
+    $$css: true
+  }, {}]
+};
+```
+
+This correctly concatenates to `"xcu4pi3 x1cbl2y9"` which matches both CSS classes.
+
+## Root Cause
+
+The issue was introduced in commit 7a1ed95a where the code that handles dynamic styles was refactored. The original code added a space suffix to each class except the last one:
+
+```javascript
+const suffix = index === classList.length - 1 ? '' : ' ';
+// ...
+t.stringLiteral(cls + suffix)
+```
+
+However, in the refactored version, this space handling was removed, causing classes to be concatenated without spaces.
+
+## Solution
+
+The fix adds spaces between classes in the `exprList` during the forEach loop in `/testbed/packages/@stylexjs/babel-plugin/src/visitors/stylex-create.js`:
+
+```javascript
+classList.forEach((cls, index) => {
+  // ... existing code to add the class ...
+  
+  // Add space after class, except for the last one
+  if (index < classList.length - 1) {
+    exprList.push(t.stringLiteral(' '));
+  }
+});
+```
+
+This ensures that when the expressions are reduced using the `+` operator, spaces are properly inserted between class names.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+1. **File Modified**: `/testbed/packages/@stylexjs/babel-plugin/src/visitors/stylex-create.js`
+   - Added space insertion logic in the `classList.forEach` loop (lines 350-353)
+
+2. **Tests Updated**: 6 snapshot tests were updated to reflect the correct output with spaces
+
+## Verification
+
+All existing tests pass, including:
+- 700+ passing tests
+- 673 passing snapshots
+- All dynamic style tests with media queries, pseudo-classes, and pseudo-elements
+
+The fix correctly handles:
+- Single class (no unnecessary spaces)
+- Multiple classes with media queries
+- Multiple classes with pseudo-classes
+- Multiple classes with pseudo-elements
+- Mixed dynamic and static properties
+- Four or more conditional styles
